WEBVTT

00:00.868 --> 00:02.677
NARRATOR:
In the criminal justice system

00:02.735 --> 00:06.616
the people are represented by two
separate yet equally important groups,

00:06.740 --> 00:08.515
the police who
investigate crime

00:08.609 --> 00:11.249
and the district attorneys
who prosecute the offenders.

00:11.478 --> 00:12.980
These are their stories.

00:13.914 --> 00:16.793
Fifteen people?
I cooked enough for 50.

00:16.850 --> 00:18.454
You think anyone eats it?

00:18.585 --> 00:20.189
So concerned if
they're gonna fit

00:20.254 --> 00:21.824
into their tiny little clothes.

00:21.922 --> 00:23.367
Well, I guess
a rehearsal dinner,

00:23.423 --> 00:26.427
Mr. and Mrs. Vance want to make
sure they put out a good spread.

00:26.493 --> 00:29.167
Honey, if I had that spread
when I was getting married,

00:29.229 --> 00:31.641
my man might've stayed
just for the leftovers.

00:31.698 --> 00:32.698
(LAUGHING)

00:34.501 --> 00:37.311
Oh! Sweet Jesus!

00:37.471 --> 00:39.280
It's Christy Garrison!

00:39.339 --> 00:41.341
Quick, get Mr. Vance!

00:41.909 --> 00:43.911
Christy Garrison, 15.

00:43.977 --> 00:46.253
ID'd by her dad,
Michael Garrison.

00:46.313 --> 00:49.123
You read about him? Guy's
worth half a billion dollars.

00:49.182 --> 00:51.321
Another lesson in
what money can't buy.

00:51.385 --> 00:52.796
He the suit or the blue shirt?

00:52.853 --> 00:55.629
Blue shirt. Guy in the suit
is Mark Vance, the neighbor.

00:55.689 --> 00:57.327
That the lady who
found the girl?

00:57.391 --> 01:00.065
Yeah, Vondie Morris.
She's the Vances' cook.

01:00.193 --> 01:02.434
She wrings her hands one more
time, they're gonna fall off.

01:02.963 --> 01:04.271
Anything in her pockets?

01:04.331 --> 01:06.504
20 bucks.
An inhaler, full.

01:06.567 --> 01:08.740
BRISCOE: Ah, asthma. Sex?

01:08.969 --> 01:11.074
Don't know. Clothes aren't
torn, her nails look fine.

01:11.138 --> 01:12.412
No sign of a struggle.

01:12.506 --> 01:15.248
Yeah, except somebody
clocked her against the wall.

01:15.375 --> 01:18.379
Well, no robbery.
Her jewelry's still on.

01:18.679 --> 01:20.386
Stick here, Agnelli. Be nice.

01:21.515 --> 01:23.995
Miss Morris, uh,
you came outside...

01:24.051 --> 01:26.964
At 7:30. I let Nell
in, another maid.

01:27.020 --> 01:28.897
I'm a live-in.
Nell, she lives out.

01:29.022 --> 01:31.593
You see or hear anything last night?
Early this morning?

01:31.658 --> 01:34.264
No. I was tired.
Had an early night.

01:34.628 --> 01:35.698
You knew this girl?

01:35.762 --> 01:39.300
I've seen her time to time.
Outside smoking, that's all.

01:40.233 --> 01:42.804
Do you need me? I got breakfast
to put on the table.

01:42.869 --> 01:44.177
No. Maybe later. Thanks.

01:44.271 --> 01:45.579
ED: ...doing outside in
the middle of the night?

01:45.639 --> 01:46.709
I don't know what she
was doing outside

01:46.773 --> 01:48.184
in the middle of
the night, Detective.

01:48.241 --> 01:49.413
We all went to bed early.

01:49.476 --> 01:52.013
We had dinner together
last night. Our house.

01:52.646 --> 01:53.750
Both families. Everyone.

01:53.814 --> 01:55.816
Anybody have a bedroom
faces the alley?

01:56.350 --> 01:59.092
Yes, we do. But we
didn't hear anything.

01:59.353 --> 02:02.926
You go in, Mr. Garrison. You be with your family.
We'll be in shortly.

02:03.924 --> 02:05.528
Is that gate locked
all the time?

02:05.726 --> 02:06.796
Yes.

02:07.761 --> 02:10.833
Uh, who has access
to it from the outside?

02:11.231 --> 02:13.609
Immediate families.
Mine, Michael's.

02:13.967 --> 02:16.243
My chauffeur, Sammy. He's the
only one with an opener.

02:16.303 --> 02:17.441
Could you get him, please?

02:17.504 --> 02:19.780
He's not here yet.
He was due at 6:30.

02:19.840 --> 02:21.183
He late a lot?

02:21.241 --> 02:22.413
Not like this.

02:22.476 --> 02:24.513
He comes, takes the limo out
of the garage, pulls it up.

02:24.611 --> 02:26.022
Can we see the limo?

02:26.079 --> 02:27.285
Yes, of course.

02:28.782 --> 02:30.159
Sammy been with you long?

02:30.250 --> 02:32.787
Since the beginning of the year.
He's Vondie's son.

02:36.123 --> 02:39.002
Why do I get the feeling Sammy
won't be calling in sick?

